I thought this would be a good tool to refresh and keep updated with programming. But its tutorials are all pretty basic, and the challenges are user-generated, meaning they fail to demonstrate good coding practices and are nothing more than time-limited "gotchas" using obtuse, deliberately poorly written code to catch out the unwary (and not to encourage good code, best practice or proper learning). Feedback gets no response, it's just a tool to make money from pushing ads. Avoid, uninstall.
